  <sect1 id="partitions">
    <title>Manipulating Partitions</title>
    
    <sect2 id="adding-partition">
      <title>Creating a Partition</title>
      <para>
	Adding a partition is easy with the help of Ximian Setup Tools.  Press
	<guibutton>Add Button</guibutton> to get started.
      </para>
      <para>
	Chances are you will leave the <guilabel>Type</guilabel> alone.  This will
	detect the format for you.  The device is what partition on the hard disk
	to access, such as /dev/hda1.  The mount point is the directory that the
	partition will represent.
      </para>
    </sect2>
    
    <sect2 id="editing-partitions">
      <title>Editing Partitions</title>
      <para>
	Editing a partition is very similar to creating a new partition.  As a
	matter of fact, they use the same interface for both functions.  Refer to
	the section on adding a partition <!-- insert link --> for more
	information on editing partitions.  <!-- wording sucks -->
      </para>
    </sect2>
